The dataset provides three data tables including orde_shipment, inventory and fulfillment. After examining the data fields, I noticed that the dataset generally represents the following key information

Customer: General customers information about including identifiers and addresses

Order: order Information including order date , product and quantity ordered, order value

Shipment: Shipping information including shipping date, shipping mode

Product: Specific information about the ordered item including product name, product category, product department

Warehouse Inventory: Information on inventory management for each product name including monthly inventory, warehouse location, storage costs, order fulfillment

#Create shipping time feature
orders_shipment['shipping_time'] = pd.to_datetime(orders_shipment['shipment_date']) - pd.to_datetime(orders_shipment['order_date'])
orders_shipment['shipping_time'] = orders_shipment['shipping_time'].dt.days

#Create delay shipment feature
def calculate_delay(row):
    if row['shipping_time'] > row["shipment_days_scheduled"]:
        return 'Late'
    else:
        return 'On time'

orders_shipment['delay_Shipment'] = orders_shipment.apply(calculate_delay, axis=1)
